Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.28,0:00:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In this update,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.29,0:00:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to talk about how we can make
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.32,0:00:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,good use of our time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.42,0:00:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,during the pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, we’d like to share a few updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.40,0:00:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sad to report that, as of December 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.57,0:00:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we have lost 25,658
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.97,0:00:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,brothers and sisters to COVID-19.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.64,0:00:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Our prayers are certainly with all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who have lost loved ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.82,0:00:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, the new Omicron variant
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has received a lot of news coverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.46,0:00:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, there are still many unknowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.33,0:00:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters, we don’t need to panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.87,0:00:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep following the same basic precautions\Nthat have worked well:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,wearing masks,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.71,0:00:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,physical distancing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.81,0:01:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,frequently washing our hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting vaccinated, if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.88,0:01:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}2021 Governing Body Update #7,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.62,0:01:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lösch mentioned that over 80 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.42,0:01:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the worldwide Bethel family\Nwas vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.83,0:01:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We are glad to inform you\Nthat now over 99 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.20,0:01:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of our worldwide Bethel family is vaccinated,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.30,0:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and so are over 95 percent of our
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.44,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,special full-time servants in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.94,0:01:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of our brothers and sisters have had
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.58,0:01:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,good results from being vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.02,0:01:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.02,0:01:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in some parts of Bulgaria,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.46,0:01:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the local clergy say that vaccines
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.06,0:01:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,are “poison from the Devil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.13,0:01:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is much pressure in the community
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.56,0:01:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}not {\r} to get vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.70,0:02:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite this, one sister and her husband
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.50,0:02:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,watched the Governing Body updates
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.51,0:02:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and made their personal decision\Nto get vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, the sister’s employer called her
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.65,0:02:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and said that in order\Nto comply with government regulations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,she couldn’t return to work\Nif she had not been vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How surprised the manager was to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.89,0:02:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that the sister was already vaccinated!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.76,0:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.77,0:02:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,she was the only employee who was vaccinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone else had to be laid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.61,0:02:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The manager asked our sister
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.91,0:02:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if she had any vaccinated friends\Nwho could replace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.75,0:02:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the employees who had been fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The manager then called other Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that she knew to see if they had any
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.32,0:02:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,vaccinated friends who needed employment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:02:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.83,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly all the positions were filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The head of staff asked our sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“How do you know so many vaccinated women?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.17,0:03:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A fine witness was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.61,0:03:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, 14 sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.31,0:03:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and 1 Bible student were employed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.85,0:03:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they followed\Nthe good guidance and Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been shared\Nin our various Governing Body updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.63,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s get back to our topic\Nof putting our time to good use
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,during the pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been exciting to hear how many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,have reached out to pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,started new study projects,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.01,0:03:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and refined your telephone\Nand letter-writing skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.95,0:03:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is time well spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s update,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.35,0:03:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we will discuss two additional ways
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we can use our time wisely:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,helping inactive ones
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.63,0:04:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and improving our reading and writing skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.53,0:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been wonderful to see so many\Nof our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,who were inactive begin associating
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with us again during the pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.01,0:04:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If that describes you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,please know
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Governing Body\Nwarmly welcomes you back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the joy that Jehovah, Jesus,\Nand all the angels
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in heaven have experienced\Nat seeing you return.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about those\Nwho have not yet returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They might feel like the psalmist,\Nas recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.44,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 119:176.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.67,0:04:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There we read:\N“I have strayed like a lost sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.38,0:04:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Search for your servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.02,0:05:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for I have not forgotten your commandments.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, some inactive ones\Nmay be praying to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,saying: ‘Search for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I need help to come back.’
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.46,0:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven’t forgotten Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.13,0:05:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but for various reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.37,0:05:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they haven’t been able\Nto come back on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah feel about such ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezekiel 34:15, 16 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“I myself will feed my sheep . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“The lost one I will search for,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“the stray I will bring back,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“the injured I will bandage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the weak I will strengthen.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can Jehovah use you to find his lost sheep?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.94,0:05:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you have\Nreached out to inactive ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.61,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following video,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.61,0:06:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how publishers took the initiative
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.41,0:06:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to help others return to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.78,0:06:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what my brother was ever
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.02,0:06:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do about the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.82,0:06:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As a teenager, he was a publisher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.49,0:06:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he was 16,\Nsadly, he decided to leave home,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.89,0:06:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he no longer served Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, when we came back\Nto Seattle and settled down,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then we had more contact with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.27,0:06:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I\Nhad been providing meals for him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because his wife had a brain tumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.21,0:06:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But the beautiful thing\Nis that our congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.74,0:06:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,started taking him meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.61,0:06:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When my brother’s wife was hospitalized,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they even assisted at the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit him and give him encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.65,0:06:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That had a big impact upon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He could see the closeness\Nof the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think that built a desire\Nthat he would really like to do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:06:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When my brother went to the Kingdom Hall,\Nhe was only able to do that 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.10,0:06:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for two weeks\Nand then COVID-19 struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.40,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But an elder talked to him the first time\Nhe went to the Kingdom Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and they exchanged phone numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they were able to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that elder helped set him up on Zoom,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.05,0:07:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was able to attend the meetings then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.08,0:07:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went to all the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I encouraged him\Nto have a personal study,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and he said, “Well I’m doing my study.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all things, it was a terminology issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t know about having\Na personal Bible study with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He had some more encouragement\Nfrom a family friend
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that found out\Nthat he was coming to meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he started to have\Nhis own Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s when he really started\Nto make progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It took 59 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.98,0:07:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege of actually performing\Nthe baptism for my own brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At the beginning of the pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we knew that our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was going to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.65,0:07:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we thought about what to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.66,0:07:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we came up with this little project,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.09,0:07:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,making a list of all the inactive people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.73,0:08:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could think of that we’d been\Nwith in other congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—lots of young people and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.23,0:08:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we did that list,\Nthere were about 40 people on that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’ve emailed, we’ve called,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve texted,\Nand we’ve written lots of letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.98,0:08:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them, we haven’t heard anything from,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but nobody has rejected our efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I contacted one man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.82,0:08:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whom I had met almost 40 years ago\Nwhen I was 19 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We reestablished contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.96,0:08:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He began to attend all the meetings on Zoom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.36,0:08:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we’re studying the Bible\Nin the En{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}joy Life Forever!  {\r}book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We contacted one brother\Nwho’d been inactive for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he attends all the meetings on Zoom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.84,0:08:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He has been reactivated,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.11,0:08:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of this despite\Nsome very serious health problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.78,0:08:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Patience and persistence are required
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.85,0:08:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when reaching out to these dear ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We love them, and so we contact
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.75,0:09:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,some on that list every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.49,0:09:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.63,0:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Three of the persons that we’ve contacted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,are now regularly attending the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.70,0:09:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of them are studying the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s really been encouraging\Nfor us to see these ones
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.64,0:09:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that we love so much return to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.44,0:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And really, if Jehovah is drawing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.38,0:09:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re going to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you agree
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.85,0:09:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah blessed these efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.12,0:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach out to his lost sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful way to use our time
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,during the pandemic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.23,0:09:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One circuit overseer in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,recently reported that 76 individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in his circuit have been reactivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the equivalent\Nof an entire congregation!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.51,0:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage you\Nto prayerfully think of inactive ones
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:09:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that you might know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:10:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a family member or friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.75,0:10:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give them a call
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.89,0:10:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or send them a letter or a text message?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.19,0:10:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they respond and attend a meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,make them feel welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope that many more lost sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.73,0:10:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will return to Jehovah before the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Another good use of our time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.87,0:10:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is improving our reading and writing skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.21,0:10:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading and writing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.21,0:10:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has always been important\Nfor Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.12,0:10:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the kings of Israel were told
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to “write [out] . . . a copy of [the] Law” 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and “read from it\Nall the days of [their] life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.39,0:10:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was raised by a poor family,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.06,0:10:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,yet he was able to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We remember the time when he went\Ninto the synagogue in Nazareth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.60,0:10:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He was able to open the Isaiah scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:10:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—which had no chapters and verses—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and locate and read the correct scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s not forget what Paul told Timothy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.58,0:11:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Timothy was already an elder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.52,0:11:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Paul said to him:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.89,0:11:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue applying yourself\Nto public reading.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.93,0:11:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So in view\Nof the Bible’s emphasis on reading,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not surprising that God’s organization
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.57,0:11:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has a wonderful history of helping people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.14,0:11:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the world to learn to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.81,0:11:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the past 70 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses have taught\Nthousands of people worldwide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.79,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we have helped more than 156,000 people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn to read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.10,0:11:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve received awards\Nin several countries for our efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.10,0:12:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that now in many languages
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.84,0:12:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we have technology that enables us\Nto listen to our publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don’t want to be content to rely
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.18,0:12:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on audio publications alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.55,0:12:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to be able to read\Nand to study the Bible for ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and to dig into the wonderful information
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,provided by “the faithful\Nand discreet slave.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some other benefits that come
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.46,0:12:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from learning to read well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.33,0:12:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A new article was recently published
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on jw.org entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why Reading Is Important for Children.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This was prepared\Nwith you dear parents in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.81,0:12:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But, really, reading is something
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.85,0:12:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}all{\r}  of us should view as important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The article explained that reading\Nstirs the imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.06,0:13:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It builds character 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.43,0:13:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and helps us to reason on our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.33,0:13:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps us develop qualities\Nsuch as patience,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.17,0:13:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,self-control, and empathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And reading promotes deep thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.21,0:13:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,During the pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.25,0:13:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,some of our brothers have been making\Ngood use of their time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by learning to read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s hear how they have benefited.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.39,0:13:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When the coronavirus broke out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.23,0:13:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the country, schools were shut down 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.46,0:13:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and many parents either couldn’t go to work 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.77,0:13:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or they had to work from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.33,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One circuit overseer set a goal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage the parents in his circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.81,0:13:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to take advantage of the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.81,0:13:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry on teaching\Ntheir children to read and write
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,with the objective of assisting them\Nto become publishers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.45,0:13:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Many parents responded\Nto the encouragement, and this resulted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.98,0:13:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in 37 young ones becoming proficient\Nin reading and writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.95,0:14:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister named Sara
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,had been trying for some time to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At home, her husband tried to help her,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but they just couldn’t find enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.27,0:14:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their day-to-day activities\Nand many responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when the pandemic
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.87,0:14:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,limited their activities,\Nher husband, who is an elder,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,took advantage of the extra time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He began to help her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.75,0:14:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,several times a week to learn to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.02,0:14:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now she has the joy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of reading the Bible\Nand other publications on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.36,0:14:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She also loves to sing the Kingdom songs
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,using her own songbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One Bible student named Comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,earnestly longed\Nto be able to read the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She became downhearted\Nwhen the pandemic began
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and wondered who was going\Nto help her read now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that she couldn’t physically attend\Na literacy class.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.34,0:14:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A local congregation elder gave her\Nsome excellent practical suggestions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and he encouraged her\Nto continue practicing on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With determination and persistence,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.98,0:15:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Comfort applied the suggestions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.99,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She made steady progress,\Nand she now reads well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.62,0:15:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She conducts five Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She is also assisting\Nher own 14-year-old daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn how to read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.20,0:15:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Comfort was baptized
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at the 2020 “Always Rejoice”!\NRegional Convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.53,0:15:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria is our 69-year-old sister in Nicaragua,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.04,0:15:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and she’s been a regular pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.47,0:15:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for over six years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.67,0:15:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She never had formal schooling,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and so she learned to read\Nas she studied the Bible with our sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.25,0:15:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but she didn’t learn to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.82,0:15:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When the pandemic started,\NMaria was very discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.09,0:15:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because she didn’t know\Nhow to use her cell phone to preach,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.09,0:15:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and she didn’t know how to write letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.93,0:15:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But some of her fellow pioneers\Noffered to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So Maria would dictate her words\Nto her field service partner
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who would then write the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.57,0:15:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Her field service partners\Nwould send Maria photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.77,0:15:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the letters they wrote in her behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:16:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And using the photographs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.41,0:16:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria would then copy them\Nso as to write her own letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.45,0:16:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This helped Maria\Nto start developing writing skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.25,0:16:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She now writes her own letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could see the letters that she writes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what neat handwriting she’s learned
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.89,0:16:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to have, and how well she expresses herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, she has Jehovah’s blessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.60,0:16:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s certainly an encouragement\Nto all of us to try to continue to improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful way to use\Nour time during the pandemic!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s not\N—even for a minute—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,think that literacy is an issue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in only a few parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.42,0:16:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, literacy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is an issue {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.92,0:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And, if we’re being honest with ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,probably most of us would say
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could improve\Nin our reading and writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.27,0:17:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So why not make the effort to do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.77,0:17:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Note what the Governing Body said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in a recent letter to all Branch Committees:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“We want our brothers and sisters\Nto progress spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.08,0:17:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“and grow to maturity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“In large measure, this requires\Nthat they be able to read
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.69,0:17:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and study God’s Word\Nalong with our publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.66,0:17:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Many of the ways in which we serve God
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.46,0:17:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“involve the ability to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“all Christians have\Nthe weighty responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.84,0:17:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“of teaching vital truths to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.34,0:17:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“And appointed men have many responsibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.28,0:17:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“that involve reading. . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“In general,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians should be able to read.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.52,0:17:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could we learn to read\Nor improve in our reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are two ways:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask a friend, a family member,\Nor someone in your congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.23,0:18:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.27,0:18:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,An excellent tool
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to assist is the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Apply Yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.20,0:18:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}to Reading and Writing{\r} brochure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It is available in 123 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not ask your congregation elders
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to obtain this brochure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.15,0:18:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you already know the alphabet\Nand you can recognize words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.42,0:18:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,audio recordings\Nof our literature may also help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.36,0:18:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As you listen to the recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.89,0:18:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,read along in the written publication.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Work to imitate the pronunciation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.83,0:18:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as you hear each word.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.57,0:18:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Improving our reading and writing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.97,0:18:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great way to use our time\Nduring the pandemic!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.18,0:18:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You brothers and sisters have shown
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can thrive spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:18:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and build others up\Nduring a time of adversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have made good use of your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.39,0:19:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,May all of us continue to do so
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by assisting inactive ones
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and by improving our reading skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.93,0:19:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be assured
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.00,0:19:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Governing Body keeps\Nall of you in our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.67,0:19:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting®.
